body.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black Panda (2021)
body.description:
From the school-spirited College Colors Program to the vibrant Nike CO.JP collection, Nike Dunks have seen many colorways since the design‚Äôs inception in 1985. But with each new colorway, the Dunk‚Äôs classic color-blocking has remained in some capacity. Nike put its timeless color-blocking to work with the Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black.

The upper Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black is constructed of white leather with black leather overlays and Swooshes. Classic Nike branding is featured on the nylon tongue, nodding to traditional Dunk design elements. A white midsole and black outsole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black released in January of 2021 and retailed for $100.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx
body.description:
First revealed in February 2022 at the Donda 2 listening event in Miami, the adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx features an all-black foam construction with a soft footbed for comfort. At the base, a grooved outsole adds stability and responsiveness.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Onyx released in March of 2022 and retailed for $60.

body.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 White
body.description:
The Nike Air Force 1 Low White ‚Äò07 features an all-white leather upper with a perforated toe box and Swoosh overlays. A Nike heel embroidery and white sole completes the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low White ‚Äò07 originally released in 2007, but since it is an essential colorway to the brand, it consistently restocks.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair)
body.description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.
The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair) features a slightly different composition than the original adidas Yeezy Slide Pure that debuted in the spring of 2021. Instead of a smooth EVA foam construction, it has a pebbled, more textural touch. At the base, a grooved sole and cushioned footbed completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Pure (Restock Pair) released in December of 2021 and retailed for $60.

To shop the original adidas Yeezy Slide Pure, click here.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low White Black (2021) (W)
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women‚Äôs sneaker features a white and black leather upper with perforations on the toe box. The base of the upper starts with white leather, and black leather wraps around it in an even pattern. A black Nike Swoosh logo adorns either side of the upper and wraps around the ankle to complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low White Black 2021 women‚Äôs sneaker released in March of 2021 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Bleached Coral
body.description:
Following the classic Black Toe theme, the Air Jordan 1 High OG Bleached Coral features a smooth white leather upper with black overlays and light grey Durabuck heel wraps. Tradition Nike woven tongue labels and Jordan Wings Logos on the collars add a retro feel. From there, a white and light grey Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 High OG Bleached Coral releases in July of 2022 and retails for $180.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Onyx
body.description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Onyx arrives with an Onyx, oval-cut foam construction made of part EVA and algae. At the base, a cushioned footbed offers comfort and support, while a sculptural sole with deep treads provides traction.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Onyx released in June of 2022 and retailed for $80.

body.name: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black
body.description:
Jordan Brand flipped one of its original Air Jordan 4 colorways for the Air Jordan 4 Military Black.

Pulling its color-blocked style from the Air Jordan 4 Military Blue, the Air Jordan 4 Military Black features a smooth white leather upper with a light grey Durabuck toe wrap and netted TPU inserts. Military Black eyelets, heel tabs, and underlays add a stark contrast to the upper. At the base, a white, black, and light grey sole with a visible Air unit completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Military Black released in May of 2022 and retailed for $210.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Chlorophyll
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Chlorophyll features a light green smooth leather upper with darker green overlays and white Swooshes. Woven tongue labels and Nike embroideries on the heel tabs add a retro look. At the base, a white and green foam sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Chlorophyll released in 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS)
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) silhouette comes in a stark black and white colorway and is made from premium leather materials throughout. Additionally, white Nike lettering complements the rear ankle support of the silhouette while the Nike Air text along with the customary company Swoosh logo adorns the tongue. In keeping with the color scheme, a white midsole resting atop a black outsole rounds out the look of this Dunk Low Retro shoe.

The Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (GS) released in March of 2021 and retailed for $85.

body.name: Jordan 4 Retro Infrared
body.description:
The Air Jordan 4 Infrared features a tonal grey Durabuck upper with black TPU mesh inserts, tech straps, and heel tabs. Hits of Infrared on the lacing system and woven Jordan Flight tongue label add a sharp contrast to the neutral-toned base. From there, a white sole with visible Air units completes the design.

The Air Jordan 4 Infrared released in June of 2022 and retailed for $200.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Valerian Blue
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Valerian Blue arrives in a smooth white leather construction with deep Valerian Blue overlays and Swooshes. Hits of red on the woven tongue label and heel embroidery add a subtle contrast. At the base, a matching white and blue Air sole completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Valerian Blue released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Coconut Milk
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Coconut Milk features an off-white tumbled leather upper with pale yellow overlays and white Swooshes. Woven tongue labels and heel embroideries nod to the original 1985 design. From there, a matching Air sole at the base completes the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Coconut Milk released in March of 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Glow Green (2022) (Restock)
body.description:
DISCLAIMER: US and UK sizing is the same and does not require any conversion.
The Yeezy Slide Glow (2022 Restock) arrives as a more vibrant variation of the 2021 Yeezy Slide Glow. It is constructed with a Glow EVA foam for comfort and responsiveness. A grooved outsole adds proper traction for daily wear.

The Yeezy Slide Glow (2022 Restock) released in May of 2022 and retailed for $60.

body.name: New Balance 550 Cream Black
body.description:
The New Balance 550 Cream Black features a smooth white leather upper with perforated overlays, black piping, mesh collars, and cracked leather New Balance logos. At the tongue, a New Balance Basketball woven label adds a vintage feel. From there, a matching sole with court grip completes the design.

The New Balance 550 Cream Black released in March of 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone
body.description:
The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone features a triple white Primeknit upper with mesh side stripes and canvas heel tabs. At the base, a semi-translucent sole with Boost technology completes the design.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Bone released in March of 2022 and retailed for $230.

body.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White
body.description:
Supreme and Nike paid homage to an NYC classic with the release of the Nike Air Force 1 Low Supreme White, now available on StockX. This collaboration adds Supreme‚Äôs world-renowned Box Logo to the side of a traditional all-white Air Force 1 design.

This Air Force 1 Low is comprised of an all-white leather upper with matching soles and detailing. A red Supreme Box Logo placed on the outside heel completes the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $96.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage
body.description:
The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage features a sculptural EVA foam and algae blended construction that arrives in a Stone Sage monochromatic color scheme. From there, a grooved outsole provides traction and support.

The adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Stone Sage released in March of 2022 and retailed for $90.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Onyx
body.description:
With a triple black Primeknit upper, the adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Onyx takes it back to the basics, using its muted palette to emphasize the intricacies of its construction. A sheer mesh side stripe and canvas heel loop offer a subtle contrast in texture. At the base, a matching signature Boost sole provides comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy 350 V2 Onyx released in the Spring of 2022 and retailed for $220.

body.name: Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS)
body.description:
The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black for Grade Schoolers (GS) for grade schoolers first was sold on the market in May of 2022.

This unique shoe model provides a modern spin on the original retro item that was created in 1989. It features a white sole and base with suede and leather overlays in neutral shades of beige and black. The Air Jordan 4 Retro Military Black (GS) for grade schoolers has mesh side panels that were designed not only for style, but also for their breathability. The model provides the feet with plenty of support for walking and exercise.

The retail price for this item started at $210 for adult sizes.

body.name: New Balance 550 White Grey
body.description:
The New Balance 550 White Grey features a white leather upper with monochromatic perforated leather overlays and puffed New Balance logos. From there, a woven New Balance Basketball tongue label and matching sole completes the design.

The New Balance 550 White Grey released in June of 2021 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Nike Dunk High Black White (2021)
body.description:
The Nike Dunk High Black White 2021features a smooth white leather upper with perforations on the toe box. Black leather overlays, eyestays and Swooshes match the black laces. Orange hits on the insole add the Total Orange to the vintage White/Black colorway. The rubber outsole is black with a concentric-circles pattern for traction. The midsole is white with visible threading around the shoe. Black Nike branding appears on the white tongue and the heel features a black loop with arcs of white-on-white horizontal threading below it.

¬† The Nike Dunk High Black White 2021 was released on January 27, 2022 at a retail price of $115.

body.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black Black
body.description:
The all-black Air Force 1 Low is a timeless classic in Nike's catalog of heritage sneakers.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Black features a triple black smooth leather upper with a matching Air sole and laces. Subtle Nike Air embroidery on the heel tab nods to the history of the AF-1 line. A metallic lace tag and woven tongue label complete the design.

The Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 retails for $90.

body.name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Patent Bred
body.description:
The Air Jordan 1 High Bred Patent features black and red patent leather upper with signature weaved Nike Air tongue labels. From there, a classic Wings logo on the collar and a white with red Air sole complete the retro design.

The Air Jordan 1 High Bred Patent releases in December of 2021 and retails for $170.

body.name: Nike SB Dunk Low Los Angeles Dodgers
Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper (W)
body.description:
The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper arrives in a classic two-tone color blocked look similar to the original Nike Dunks of the 1980s. This Dunk offers a warm palette primed for the summer weather, with a white and Rose Whisper leather construction. Matching woven tongue labels contribute to the design's retro feel, while an EVA foam sole provides cushioning.

The women's Nike Dunk Low Rose Whisper released in June of 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra
body.description:
Debuted in 2017, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra is known as one of the most renowned colorways in the Yeezy line. It features a white and black marbled Primeknit upper with a white side-stripe and red "SPLY-350" text. At the base, a cushioned Boost sole provides comfort and support.

The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Zebra released in February of 2017 and retailed for $220.

body.name: adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre
body.description:
The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre is constructed entirely of EVA foam in a monochromatic fashion. A soft footbed offers immediate step-in comfort for daily wear. From there, deep groove treads on the sole provide traction and support.

The adidas Yeezy Slide Ochre released in December of 2021 and retailed for $60.

body.name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Mystic Navy
body.description:
The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy arrives in a black and Mystic Blue smooth leather construction with identical color blocking and detailing to the original line of 1985 Air Jordan 1s. At the heel, a classic Jordan Wings logo nods to the silhouette's origins. From there, a white and Mystic Navy Air sole completes the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Low Mystic Navy released in June of 2022 and retailed for $130.

body.name: Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021)
body.description:
Since its debut in 2001, the Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey has become one of the most celebrated colorways in the Jordan 11 catalog.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) features a Cool Grey Durabuck upper with patent leather overlays and a signature Jumpman embroidery on the collar. From there, a white midsole and an icy blue translucent outsole complete the design.

The Air Jordan 11 Cool Grey (2021) released in December of 2021 and retails for $225.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Black White (2022)
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Black features a black tumbled leather upper with smooth leather overlays and white Swooshes. From there, matching woven tongue labels and EVA foam soles complete the design.

The Nike Dunk Low Black released in May of 2022 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite
body.description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite has toe cap, collar flaps, eyestays, and heel counter fashioned with a buttery "Light Smoke Grey" leather. The shoe's upper base features a clean white leather that pops out of the toe box and mid-quarter panel. Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite adds a striking contrast with its pitch-black Swoosh. It also features a black shade on the sock liner, tongue, and collar. The white and Light Smoke Grey midsole adds to the overall greyscale look. The shoe features a white Jumpman on the tongue tab and a white "Wings" logo on the collar flap.

Released in April, 2020, the Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite had a retail price of $120.

body.name: Nike Dunk Low Teal Zeal (W)
body.description:
The Nike Dunk Low Teal Zeal (Women's) offers a vibrant palette with a smooth white leather upper and bright teal tumbled leather overlays and Swooshes. Hits of bright yellow on the woven tongue label and outsole add a warm contrast. Nike heel embroideries nod to the original 1985 design, adding the finishing touch.

The Nike Dunk Low Teal Zeal (Women's) released in July of 2022 and retailed for $110.

body.name: Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe
body.description:
The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe takes cues from the 2018 Air Jordan 1 High Bred Toe with its signature black and red color blocking. The upper is composed of white, black, and red leather, with black and red leather smothering the vamp, Swoosh, and heel while white leather is prominent on the quarter panel. From there, an embroidered Wing logo on the heel and a Jumpman tongue label complete the design.

The Jordan 1 Low Bred Toe released in December of 2021 and retailed for $100.

body.name: Jordan 2 Retro SP Maison Chateau Rouge
body.description:
In collaboration with Paris-based boutique and fashion label Maison Ch√¢teau Rouge, the Air Jordan 2 Maison Ch√¢teau Rouge celebrates global youth culture with its playful palette and unique detailing. It features an off-white leather upper with textural overlays, light grey suede mud guards, and orange suede toe and heel wraps. From there, brogue-style perforations and zig-zagged eyestays add a luxurious feel, while hand-stitched detailing channels a DIY element.

The Air Jordan 2 Maison Ch√¢teau Rouge released in July of 2022 and retailed for $225.
